<exercise checkit-seed="0000" checkit-slug="DL4" checkit-title="Using Laplace Transforms to Solve IVPs">
  <statement>
      <p>
          Explain how to solve the following IVP.
      </p>
      <me>
          -21 \, {y'} + 36 \, {y} = -3 \, {y''} + 12 \, \delta\left(t - 3\right);\qquad
          y(0)=0,
          y'(0)=1
      </me>
      <p>Hint: <m>\frac{1}{x^{2} - 7 \, x + 12} = -\frac{1}{x - 3} + \frac{1}{x - 4}</m>.</p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
      <me>
          \mathcal{L}\{y\}=\frac{4 \, e^{\left(-3 \, s\right)}}{s^{2} - 7 \, s + 12} + \frac{1}{s^{2} - 7 \, s + 12}
      </me>
      <me>
          {y} = 4 \, e^{\left(4 \, t - 12\right)} \mathrm{u}\left(t - 3\right) - 4 \, e^{\left(3 \, t - 9\right)} \mathrm{u}\left(t - 3\right) + e^{\left(4 \, t\right)} - e^{\left(3 \, t\right)}
      </me>
  </answer>
</exercise>
